title: The 2016 Fine Art Up North Calendar
text:
The 2016 Fine Art Up North Calendar Tools 
Story Published: Oct 7, 2015 at 3:29 PM EDT Story Updated: Oct 7, 2015 at 3:48 PM EDT 
An Autumn tradition, the Saint Lawrence Arts Council is selling its calendar of fine art photography of local images by local aritsts. The following images will be featured in the 2016 Fine Art Up North Calendar: –“Inner Voice,” by Sharon H.J. Cheng–“Spring Maple,” photography by Holly Chorba–“Odgensburg-Prescott International Bridge,” mixed media by Catherine LaPointe–“Old Barn,” oil painting by Kimberly LaShomb–“My Cup of Tea,” sculpture by Mary Ann and Malcolm Owen–“North Country Farms,” oil on canvas by Bill Parmer–“Canton Footbridge,” photography by Beverly Patchin–“Fall Harvest,” watercolor by Michiko Taylor–“Morning Light,” oil painting by Eric Thacher–“Adirondack Alpine,” photography by Joshua Thomas–“Sway Grass,” oil on linen by Alan Tuttle–“The Last Day of Trout Season, St. Regis River,” photography by Jan Wojcik–“Drying the Second Cut,” watercolor by Christine Zavgren
